headlines.description: — Delon Wright scored a career-high 28 points and Wayne Ellington had another impressive shooting night for Detroit, leading the Pistons to a 119-104 victory over the Eastern Conference-leading Philadelphia 76ers on Monday.

— Malcolm Brogdon scored a career-high 36 points and Myles Turner scored 11 of his 21 in the final 8 1/2 minutes Monday night to help the Indiana Pacers pull away for a 129-114 victory over the Toronto Raptors.
headlines.shortLinkText: Pacers use 4th-quarter scoring flurry, beat Raptors 129-114

headlines.description: — Nikola Vucevic scored 28 points and rookie point guard Cole Anthony added a career-high 21 points as the Orlando Magic defeated the Charlotte Hornets 117-108 on Monday night.
headlines.shortLinkText: Vucevic posts 13th double-double, Magic beat Hornets 117-108

headlines.description: — James Harden and Kevin Durant each scored 20 points despite three relatively quiet quarters, and the Brooklyn Nets broke away with a big run in the fourth to beat the Miami Heat 98-85 on Monday night.
headlines.shortLinkText: Harden, Durant help Nets break away late, beat Heat 98-85

events.name: Los Angeles Lakers at Cleveland Cavaliers

headlines.description: — LeBron James went on tear in the fourth quarter on his former home court, scoring 23 of his 46 points to keep the Los Angeles Lakers unbeaten on the road with a 115-108 win over the Cleveland Cavaliers on Monday night.
headlines.shortLinkText: LeBron scores 46, Lakers beat Cavs to stay perfect on road

headlines.description: — Jaylen Brown scored 26 points, Jayson Tatum added 24 after missing five games because of COVID-19 protocols and the Boston Celtics beat the Chicago Bulls 119-103 on Monday night.
headlines.shortLinkText: Brown, returning Tatum lead Celtics over Bulls 119-103

events.name: San Antonio Spurs at New Orleans Pelicans
Minnesota Timberwolves at Golden State Warriors

headlines.description: — Stephen Curry scored 36 points with seven 3-pointers, Andrew Wiggins took it to his old Timberwolves team for 23 points, and the Golden State Warriors beat Minnesota 130-108 on Monday night after coach Steve Kerr shook up his starting five.
headlines.shortLinkText: Wiggins takes it to Timberwolves; Warriors win 130-108

events.name: Oklahoma City Thunder at Portland Trail Blazers

headlines.description: — Shai Gilgeous-Alexander scored 24 points, Mike Muscala added 23, and the Oklahoma City Thunder snapped a three-game losing streak with a 125-122 victory over the Portland Trail Blazers on Monday night.
headlines.shortLinkText: Thunder snap 3-game skid, edge Trail Blazers 125-122
